<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1774" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1774">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/96.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Legation of Panama</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>The Department has received the memorandum of the Panaman Legation
                                dated June 17, 1915, quoting the proposition submitted to the
                                American Minister at Panama by the Secretary of Foreign Relations of
                                that Republic for the settlement of the claim growing out of the
                                events which took place at Cocoa Grove on July 4, 1912.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <dateline rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-30"><hi rend="italic">June 30, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>